  m_text: " It was invented in the late 19th century by George Babcock and Stephen
    Wilcox, and it changed how steam was generated in industries and power plants
    forever.  \r\n\r\nThis is a horizontal, water-tube boiler (where in water flows
    inside the tubes and hot gases flow outside.) with natural circulation of water.
    The water tubes are set at about 15 degrees.These can be found in power plants,
    ships, and heavy-duty industrial setups. "
